ZH: 他站在踏板上骑车。
EN: He rides a bike on the pedals.

ZH: 她的脚伤了，无法踩踏板。
EN: She injured her foot and can't pedal.

ZH: 请把脚放在踏板上。
EN: Please place your feet on the pedals.

ZH: 这个踏板设计得非常稳固。
EN: This pedal is designed very securely.

ZH: 我让踏板断了。
EN: I broke the pedal.

ZH: 自行车的踏板在哪里？
EN: Where is the bike pedal?

ZH: 这两个踏板的高度不一样。
EN: The height of these two pedals is different.

ZH: 他用力踩下踏板。
EN: He pedals hard.

ZH: 这辆自行车的踏板需要修理。
EN: The pedal of this bicycle needs repair.

ZH: 踏板上有一块脚印。
EN: There is a footprint on the pedal.

ZH: 别把踏板弄湿了。
EN: Don't get the pedal wet.

ZH: 请不要踩到踏板外面。
EN: Please do not step outside of the pedal.

ZH: 把你的脚放到踏板上并踩下去。
EN: Put your feet on the pedal and press down.

ZH: 他站在踏板上一动不动地倒数。
EN: He stood on the pedal and countdown without moving.

ZH: 小心不要把脚用力踢到踏板上。
EN: Be careful not to kick your foot hard on the pedal.

ZH: 这是一台两踏板的摩托车。
EN: This is a motorcycle with two pedals.

ZH: 骑车时，她的脚一直踩在踏板上。
EN: When cycling, her feet are always on the pedal.

ZH: 当我骑车时，我总是感觉我的脚掌贴在车踏板上。
EN: When I ride a bike, I always feel that my soles are stuck to the pedals.

ZH: 他的自行车脚踏板已经锈得很厉害了。
EN: His bike pedals have rusted badly.

ZH: 角力选手力争踏在踏板上取得优势。
EN: The wrestler strives to gain an advantage by stepping on the pedal.
